# Dr. Kriukow AI Humanization

> **Extracted from**: Dr. Jaroslaw Kriukow — Qualitative researcher and AI text humanization specialist
> **Domain**: AI content humanization, detection evasion, structural unpredictability, writing quality optimization
> **System Role**: Diagnostic safety net — use when content lacks a strong writer voice or feels AI-detectable

## Overview

This skill implements Dr. Kriukow's Statistical Unpredictability Principle (SUP): AI writing and AI detection both operate on statistical probability. The most effective humanization isn't word-swapping — it's structural divergence from the AI-generated "most predictable version."

Unlike cosmetic fixes ("avoid the word delve"), this methodology attacks the mathematical foundation of AI detection by making text structurally unpredictable at the paragraph level.

## When to Use

**Selectively** — as a diagnostic and safety net, NOT a mandatory gate on every piece of content.

| ✅ Use When | ❌ Skip When |
|------------|-------------|
| Raw AI output with no writer agent applied | Content from Nicolas Cole, Shaan Puri, Tobias Allen, etc. |
| Quick drafts you need to ship fast without a full writing pass | Anything already run through a strong voice/style skill |
| Content that "feels AI" but you can't pinpoint why | Copy that already has personality and distinctive rhythm |
| Academic or professional docs where detection is a real risk | Creative content where the voice IS the product |

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Not sure if content sounds AI | Run `structural-predictability-audit` (diagnose first) |
| Raw AI output needs humanizing | Run `ai-humanization-pass` |
| Specific paragraph needs deep rewrite | Run `meaning-extraction-rewriter` |
| New content type/voice needs calibration | Run `writing-style-humanizer-config` |

## Decision Tree

```
Content is AI-generated or AI-assisted
  │
  ├─ Was a strong writer agent used? (Nicolas Cole, Shaan Puri, etc.)
  │     ├─ YES → Skip. The writer IS the humanization.
  │     └─ NO → Continue ↓
  │
  ├─ Not sure if it sounds AI? ──→ structural-predictability-audit (diagnose first)
  │     ├─ Score LOW risk → Ship as-is
  │     └─ Score HIGH risk → Continue ↓
  │
  ├─ Quick deployment (< 500 words) ──→ ai-humanization-pass
  │
  ├─ Deep rewrite (specific paragraph) ──→ meaning-extraction-rewriter
  │
  └─ New content type/voice ──→ writing-style-humanizer-config → then ai-humanization-pass
```

## Key Principles

1. **Statistical Unpredictability over Word Swapping** — Change STRUCTURE first, vocabulary last
2. **Paragraph-Level Editing** — Never edit individual sentences in isolation; AI detectors evaluate inter-sentence relationships
3. **Meaning-First Reconstruction** — Extract what a paragraph MEANS, then re-express it differently
4. **Deliberate Imperfection** — Inject passive voice, transitional connectors, varying sentence lengths — "worse" writing is more human
5. **No Right Way** — Any structural divergence works; don't memorize specific techniques, apply the principle

